					<description><![CDATA[<p>For those with kidney failure, the wait for a new kidney can take years. There just are not enough organs from deceased donors to fill the need. Fortunately, a person can live a healthy life with just one kidney, making living-donor kidney&amp;#160;transplants&amp;#160;an alternative to deceased-donor transplants. This means a healthy kidney is removed from a [&amp;#8230;]</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/discussion/mayo-clinic-minute-what-to-expect-as-a-living-kidney-donor/">Mayo Clinic Minute: What to expect as a living kidney donor</a> appeared first on <a href="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org">Mayo Clinic News Network</a>.</p>
